This paper focuses on the evolutionary optimization of a quadruped robot controller, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of central pattern generators and sensory feedback in the control system design suggests a focus on neural networks and embodied systems (cs.NE and cs.SY). The use of evolutionary optimization also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
